This article contains information obtained from the game APIs or cache.
The content may not be currently accessible in game, or may be reserved for use in a future update.
The house and lumberyard north of Ardougne that previously belonged to Chuck, a removed character. It has remained empty since 2004.

Unused non-player characters are NPCs that exist within the game's code, but can not be found anywhere during normal gameplay. These exist for a variety of reasons; either they were removed from the game, replaced with other NPCs when an area was reworked, or were ultimately never made available ingame.

Contents

  • 3 Characters who have since been released

Characters who were never added[edit | edit source]

These characters have never been added to the game in any capacity; they are usually leftover content from development that has remained in the game files.

Picture Name Examine Release Description
Guard He tries to keep order around here. 29 March 2004 A variant of the Varrock Guards who used a crossbow. Although never released, the concept was reused in 2006 with the addition of Falador Guards who used crossbows.
Forester They love the forests. 29 March 2004 A generic version of the Forester that guards McGrubor's Wood. Unlike the normal variant, they could be attacked instead of spoken to. An updated version was later added to the Woodcutting Guild.
Knight of Ardougne To protect and serve the populace of Ardougne. 29 March 2004 An unused variant of the Knight of Ardougne. Both the animations and the head model are broken.
Barman Doesn't water down the beer too much. 29 March 2004 Unknown – may have been intended to appear somewhere in Ardougne.
Baby dragon Young but still dangerous. 29 March 2004 Similar to the Baby blue dragon, it just uses the default grey model for dragons with no recolouring.
Dryad A wood nymph. 29 March 2004 A cut race planned to be added to RuneScape 2. The concept was later recycled for the Wood Dryad in the Enchanted Valley.
Leprechaun A funny little man normally associated with rainbows. 29 March 2004 A cut race planned to be added to RuneScape 2, who had an identical appearance to Shamus. The concept was later recycled for the Tool Leprechaun.
Lizard man A scaly reptilian creature. 29 March 2004 A cut race planned to be added to RuneScape 2. The concept was later recycled for Lizardmen in Great Kourend.
Mummy A tightly wrapped monster. 29 March 2004 A cut race planned to be added to RuneScape 2, as part of "A pyramid quest in the desert full of traps, treasure and mummys". Updated versions would be added with the Desert Treasure quest in 2005.
Golem A creature made from clay. 29 March 2004 A cut race planned to be added to RuneScape 2. They had an identical appearance to the Rock golem random event, while the concept was later recycled for the Clay golem.
Dwarf A short angry guy. 29 March 2004 An unused Dwarf that had the same appearance as Mountain Dwarves, but would have been found above ground.
Skavid Servant race to the ogres. 29 March 2004 A generic version of the Skavids from the Watchtower quest. This variant could only be fought instead of talked to.
Yeti The abominable snowman. 29 March 2004 A cut race planned to be added to RuneScape 2, as part of the 'Frozen Lands' area promised in a 2004 newspost but ultimately not released. The model was reused for King Vargas, while in RuneScape Yetis would eventually be released in 2009.
Mammoth A woolly, elephantine monster. 29 March 2004 A cut race intended to be added as part of "A large 'frozen lands' area including penguins, mammoths, polar bears and more." In 2014, a different variant was created to appear in the Wilderness.
Gnome shop keeper Sells gnomish things. 29 March 2004 An unused gnome who would have sold goods within the Tree Gnome Stronghold. As all the shops are run by named characters, this gnome was never used and lacks any interaction options.
Gnome baller A professional gnome baller. 29 March 2004 A generic version of the Gnome ballers that can be found playing Gnomeball. This character, who lacks any team colours or options, may have been a placeholder until Gnome ballers with team colours were added.
Barbarian guard Not very civilised looking. 29 March 2004 A generic version of the Barbarian guard who guards the entrance to the Barbarian Outpost. They could only be attacked rather than spoken to, and were not graphically updated along with the other Barbarians in 2007.
Twig Reminds me of playing pooh sticks. 29 March 2004 Used in the Waterfall Quest, the name and examine suggest it would have been seen floating along the Baxtorian Falls.
Paladin A military man. 29 March 2004 While intended to appear during Biohazard possibly as a boss, it is unclear what the character was used for, since no Paladin appeared during the quest in RuneScape Classic.
Weapon poison salesman Supplier of deadly liquids. 29 March 2004 An unreleased shopkeeper who would have appeared in the Ranging Guild. A unique item called Display poison would have appeared at his stall.
Mist Is it a low cloud? 14 October 2004 Presumably Vampyres would have either spawned as Mist, or turned into it when defeated. This mechanic was later used for Vampyre Juvinates in 2006.
Vampyric hound And I shall call him Fang. 14 October 2004 They would presumably have been the companion of Feral Vampyres, or the Vampyre count. The character is exceptionally big, being taller than most human NPCs.
Vampire A royal pain in the neck. 14 October 2004 A Vampyre count presumably intended to appear somewhere in the Haunted Woods.
Yrsa A subject of Miscellania. 29 November 2004 An unreleased citizen of Miscellania. She may have been cut to avoid causing confusion with the character of the same name released a few weeks earlier.
Salenab It's Salenab the monkey. 6 December 2004 An unreleased monkey who would presumably have been spoken to during Monkey Madness I.
Spider It's an extremely small and probably poisonous brown spider. 6 December 2004 While spiders can be found on Ape Atoll, this version could not be fought and only examined, with a different examine information to normal spiders.
Monkey It's a monkey. 6 December 2004 A developer placeholder for standard Ape Atoll monkeys, who ultimately were not added in any form.
Monkey It's a monkey. 6 December 2004 A developer placeholder for Monkey Zombies in the Ape Atoll Dungeon; it has a different appearance to the released version.
Monkey It's a monkey. 6 December 2004 A developer placeholder for Monkey Zombies in the Ape Atoll Dungeon; it has a different appearance to the released version.

Smokedevil The cave-dwelling cousin of the dust devils. 26 January 2005 An unreleased Slayer monster; presumably, they would have been found in the Smoke Dungeon while Dust Devils would have been above ground instead. The Smoke Devil was later released in 2014.
Vulture If you see them circling... run. 26 April 2005 Although added with the release of Sophanem, it is unclear if they were actually included in the game or not. With the release of Rag and Bone Man I, new Vultures were added that landed, allowing players to obtain a Vulture wing.

Gnome shop keeper Sells gnomish things. 15 August 2006 The Gnome shop keeper was added again in 2006, presumably to appear in a cutscene during The Eyes of Glouphrie. Once again, the character failed to appear.

Characters removed before August 2007[edit | edit source]

The following characters were all present in RuneScape 2 at some stage; however, they were removed from the game before the August 2007 backup of RuneScape, and have therefore never been present in Old School RuneScape.

Picture Name Examine Release Removal Description
Barbarian Not very civilised looking. 4 January 2001 4 January 2007 The original Barbarian who could be found at the Barbarian Village and Barbarian Outpost. Although they were replaced by unique named Barbarians, the original still remains in the game files.
Witch The hat's a dead give away. 21 January 2001 20 February 2006 An attackable monster from RuneScape Classic that could be found in Draynor Manor. They were superseded by a new version when Draynor Manor was graphically updated in 2006.
Witch The hat's a dead give away. 21 January 2001 12 February 2007 An attackable monster from RuneScape Classic that could be found in a small house south of Al Kharid. When the Sorceress's Garden minigame was released, the Sorceress and the Apprentice were added to the house instead, and the Witch was removed.
Barmaid I could get a beer from her. 6 April 2001 20 February 2006 The barmaid who originally ran the Rising Sun Inn in Falador. In 2006, she was replaced by new barmaids named Emily, Kaylee, and Tina.

'''Unused non-player characters''' are NPCs that exist within the game's code, but can not be found anywhere during normal gameplay. These exist for a variety of reasons; either they were removed from the game, replaced with other NPCs when an area was reworked, or were ultimately never made available ingame.

==Characters who were never added==
These characters have never been added to the game in any capacity; they are usually leftover content from development that has remained in the game files.
